-- Several Injured After Truck Falls on Guildford to Waterloo Train Service
-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 2010-11-05T17:45:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-05/several-injured-after-truck-falls-on-guildford-to-waterloo-train-service.html
Two people are understood to have
been seriously injured while a further six people suffered minor
injuries after a cement mixer truck fell off a bridge onto a
commuter train in Oxshott, southern England.  The vehicle landed on some coaches of the 3:05 p.m.
Guildford to Waterloo service operated by South West Trains,
 Network Rail  said in a statement on its website.  British Transport Police, who are at the scene in Surrey,
said there are no reports of fatalities at this stage. The
driver and a passenger may be seriously injured and are being
treated by the ambulance service, the police said in an e-mailed
statement.  The eight-coach train is understood to have been carrying
some 40 passengers, according to the police statement. Police
officers attended the scene along with paramedics from the South
East Coast Ambulance Service and the Surrey Fire Service.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
